To give an overview of the behaviour of light at the nanoscale, including the interaction of light with nanostructures, and to introduce the audience to the current research directions and applications of nano-optics.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To give an overview of the behaviour of light at the nanoscale, including the interaction of light with nanostructures, and to introduce the audience to the current research directions and applications of nano-optics.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completing the subject, the student 1) can describe the propagation of light in dielectric media and metals.  2) can apply simple methods to calculate the propagation of light in certain optical structures (homogeneous media, layered structures).  3) knows the basic concepts of nano-optics (optical resonators, photon crystals, metamaterials, waveguides) and their applications.
